<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-08T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-08T15:00:00-05:00" n="502" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">310.2/7–854: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United
                            Nations</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lodge</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">limited official use</hi></seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-08T16:00:00-04:00">July 8, 1954—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>16. Re admission Communist China. <persName>Ardalan</persName> (Iran) says he
                        is strongly opposed to seating of Communist China. <persName corresp="#p_SERRANOFM1">Serrano</persName> (Philippines) says he is
                        against it but questioned our intention to go through. <persName corresp="#p_FORSYTHWD1">Forsyth</persName> (Australia) was surprised and
                        shocked by Foreign Minister <persName corresp="#p_WEBBTC1">Webb</persName>
                        of New Zealand’s declaration in favor of admitting Communist China.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lodge</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>